"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-break-dancing-olympic-games-paris-2024-b1169821.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Breakdancinghas attracted considerable interest since it was first announced to be added to this year's programme as a newsportfor theParis Olympics.  Its debut follows the outstanding success of the sport in the 2018 Summer Youth Olympic Games in Buenos Aires.  A fusion of acrobatic movements and stylised footwork, with a key role played by the DJ and MC during battles, breaking is an urbandancestyle from America.  It originated in the 1970s and by the 1990s, international competitions for breaking were being held, popularising the dance style and attracting global interest.  But this year, will be the first time thedanceis whirled into theOlympics.  As millions of worldwide viewers tune in to watch the games live, here's what to expect from breaking to bring you up to speed:  The breaking competition comprises two events - one for men and one for women - where 16 B-Boys and 16 B-Girls will face off in solo battles.  Hottest hotel openings for 2026  Yorke Dance Project: Modern Milestones review - lean, muscular modern dance  NBA London 2026 LIVE: Memphis Grizzlies vs Orlando Magic come to the UK  Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter  Athletes will use a combination of power moves such as windmills, the 6-step, and freezes as they adapt their style and improvise to the beat of the DJ's tracks in a bid to secure the judges' votes and take home the first Olympic breaking medals.  Competitors are judged on six criteria, including creativity, personality, technique, versatility, performance, skills and musicality.  The current schedule shows competitions over two days in August. The following UK times show when each phase will be held.  09 August:  15:00 B-Girls Round Robin  19:00 B-Girls Quarterfinal 1  19:07 B-Girls Quarterfinal 2  19:14 B-Girls Quarterfinal 3  19:21 B-Girls Quarterfinal 4  19:45 B-Girls Semifinal 1  19:52 B-Girls Semifinal 2  20:14 B-Girls Bronze Medal Battle  20:23 B-Girls Gold Medal Battle  10 August:  15:00 B-Boys Round Robin  19:00 B-Boys Quarterfinal 1  19:07 B-Boys Quarterfinal 2  19:14 B-Boys Quarterfinal 3  19:21 B-Boys Quarterfinal 4  19:45 B-Boys Semifinal 1  19:52 B-Boys Semifinal 2  20:14 B-Boys Bronze Medal Battle  20:23 B-Boys Gold Medal Battle  London is to host a week-long exhibition inMarble Archto celebrate the sport's inclusion in the Olympics.  Marble Arch London BID are hosting demonstrations between 12.30pm to 1.30pm and have arranged for breakers Breakmission 3x3s Shahii, Chris and Chuckz - also members of the award-winning breakdancing group the Gully LDN Squad - to perform.  The exhibition, Breaking Marble Arch will run from Monday, July 15 to Friday, July 19 and will take place adjacent to the Marble Arch monument.  Kay Buxton, Chief Executive, Marble Arch London BID, said:\\u00a0\\\"We are really excited to be hosting Breaking Marble Arch as we build up to the Olympic Games inParis. Breaking is a fantastic sport which combines multiple disciplines and can be done by anyone anywhere.  \\\"We are looking forward to welcoming Shahii, Chris and Chuckz to Marble Arch as they showcase some of the moves which will be on show in Paris. We encourage the whole community to come and see the talented trio in action.\\\"  Chris Arias from Gully LDN Squad, said: \\\"Gully LDN is excited to welcome a new audience to our scene, especially with breaking now being part of the Olympics. We aim to showcase how breaking has positively shaped us both physically and mentally. Join us in celebrating this dynamic sport and experience its transformative benefits.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"